"Failed to locate MTD shell process. XBM instance <>"
Perhaps someone at digital design can answer why the service cannot start? Faulty Hardware/firmware on the baseband unit?

Solution.Value:
Hi all,
I have not been involved in this ticket before, so I would try to summarize everything.
Description of sector unlock This test method only sets the sector MO admin state into Unlocked. This is required before we can do the same thing for the Cell MO. After both the Sector MO and the Cell MO is Unlocked we can setup the test models needed and perform the RF-testing. But according to the log files provided in the first mail, the error is not related to Sector Unlock. This test method PASS.
The problem you have is Setup Test model. And according to the log files there are some problems with the MTD service in the Baseband unit, so it not possible to configure the test models and thereby the test method FAILS. There could be several reasons for this. I haven't checked from witch Baseband UP the Baseband6630 is supported, but according to your logs you are running 17.Q3. According to our latest release we are using 18.Q1.C2 so this should work. The first thing to check is to run the latest released Test Program R1C (R10D will be released next week) and see if the behavior is different between 17.Q3 and 18.Q1.C2.
The problem can also be hardware Baseband 6630 related. For some reason the MDT-service won't work, but i don't know what HW/Firmware requirements in the baseband that are related to this service.
It could be some configuration errors and that we have some alarms. Unfortunately, now ESI are collected on the Basband units if it fails and no check alarms after cell unlock is implemented. This should however be corrected in R10D.
I think that we perform the following actions together, You test the unit using R10C and 18Q1.C2 and see if that solves the problem If it fails, please manually export the ESI and attach it together with all the other test program logs
(We have verified an Baseband 6630 R2A in our lab environment in R10D and it works as expected.)
If [1] don't work, we must check the ESI and perhaps remote into the test station to troubleshoot and see if it could be anything else that is test sw related.
If not [1] and [2] fix the problem --> it is Hardware related.
So start with [1] and get back to us wit the result.
Have a nice weekend
Best Regards, RC Global Test Support.
